'''''Great Expectations''''' is a [[1974 in film|1974]] film made for television based on the [[Charles Dickens]] [[Great Expectations|novel of the same name]].  It was directed by [[Joseph Hardy]], with screenwriter [[Sherman Yellen]] and music by [[Maurice Jarre]], starring [[Michael York]] as Pip and [[Sarah Miles]] as Estella. The film, made for US television but released to cinemas in the UK, broke with tradition by having the same actress play both the younger and older Estella. Simon Gipps-Kent played the young Pip and the film also starred James Mason as Magwitch and Margaret Leighton as Miss Havisham, as well as Robert Morley; Joss Ackland; Rachel Roberts; Andrew Ray; Anthony Quayle and Heather Sears. It was filmed in Eastmancolor.

